Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Roughly chop @peanuts{1/2%ounce}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Halve, core, and thinly slice @green bell pepper{1}(thinly sliced). Zest and quarter @lime{1}(zested and quartered). Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}.

> Zest one lime and quarter both for 4 servings.

Once water is boiling, add @lo mein noodles{4.5%ounce} to pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{5-7%minutes}. Drain and set aside.

While noodles cook, briefly heat a large dry pan over medium-high heat. Add peanuts and cook, stirring occasionally, until golden and fragrant, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{a large drizzle} in same pan over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites, bell pepper, and half the @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Cook, stirring, until tender and lightly browned, ~{5-7%minutes}. Transfer veggies to a plate. Reserve pan.

Add another drizzle of @cooking oil{a large drizzle} to same pan over medium-high heat. Add @ground turkey{10%ounce}; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, undisturbed, until browned on bottom, ~{3-4%minutes}. Break up into pieces; cook until cooked through, ~{2-4%minutes} more.

Stir in veggies, @sweet soy glaze{4%tablespoon}, @sweet Thai chili sauce{1%ounce}, @butter{1%tbsp}, and @Korean chili flakes{1%teaspoon} to taste. Cook, stirring, until well coated, ~{1-2%minutes}; remove from heat.

> Use 2 TBSP butter for 4 servings.

Add drained noodles, a squeeze of lime juice, and a pinch of lime zest to pan; toss to coat. Season with @salt{}.

Divide noodle stir-fry between shallow bowls.

Top with peanuts, scallion greens, and cilantro. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.

> Ground Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.